snippet.textDisplay:
Ok, so contestants paid 10k each for 75 days (on webpage). That would be 10 weeks and 1 day. Approx 1000 a week and 142 a day. So that would be 3,550 at day 25 when they were kicked out.

Hum, why did they decide to go into that house and quit their job just to get 3k? 30k I get, 10k and 3k (if they got all of pay or to the date of cancellation) I do not. I understand that challenges are paid and HOH, jury positions are paid but for the average contestant who didn't get either..that pay is pretty cheap.

I think the contestants of BBC season 8 should sue the game show. Scour the contract for possible breaches of contract and sue for damages.

They paid them peanuts, donated the winnings to charity rather than giving a good portion to the winner and contestants. What they did goes against the rules of the game.

They need look over their contracts because I'll be damned if I gave up my life to be sequestered for just 25 days, paid 3550 to 10k and didn't get an extra stipend for the abrupt end of filming where everyone was evicted with no job to go back to or way to make money as a brand new reality TV star.

Sure, they might be able to talk to gossip sites and maybe enter into other games shows but how many contestants would springboard? Do we know any reality TV celebrity that started in a big brother house?

And that's why the need to sue. They got played and discarded.
